Figure 3: Innermost loop of the model architecture which handels the individual ballistic transport of exospheric particles. “Escape” and “Cold Trapping” indicate pure loss mechanisms, which remove the respective particles from the simulation. The orange highlighted paths are indicating conversion reactions, which act as loss mechanisms for one exospheric species as well as a source mechanism of one or more other species, e.g. the photodissociation of water into atomic hydrogen and hydroxyl.




