Figure 5: Third loop of the model architecture which is iterating over all elements and all iterations of the second loop. The orange highlighted path indicates the conversion of the exospheric species into other species, which has been carried over from the inner most loop, see Figure 3. These converted particles act as a new input of source rates \(\dot s\) for subsequent iterations. Each result of the second loop is summed up to a single result for each element.




